SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 666, is
16
17
amended to read as follows:
17
18
Section 666. A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma
18
19
Commission on the Status of Women. The Commission shall consist of
19
20
thirty (30) members. The members shall be appointed as follows:
20
21
ten members appointed by the Governor, ten members appointed by the
21
22
President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and ten members appointed by
22
23
the Speaker of the House of Representatives. All members shall be
23
24
appointed by the appropriate appointing authority for a term of five
24
Req. No. 2507 Page 1

1
(5) years commencing with the date that the previous appointee’s
1
2
term expired. In making such appointments to the Commission,
2
3
consideration shall be given to making the membership broadly
3
4
representative of the geographic areas of the state and the several
4
5
racial, religious, and ethnic groups residing in the state. Each
5
6
member shall hold office until the successor of the member is
6
7
appointed and has qualified. A member of the Commission may be
7
8
removed by the appropriate appointing authority for cause. A member
8
9
appointed to fill a vacancy occurring before the expiration of a
9
10
term of a member separated from the Commission for any cause shall
10
11
be appointed for the remainder of the term of the member whose
11
12
office has been so vacated. Members of the Commission shall receive
12
13
no salary, but shall be entitled to travel reimbursement as provided
13
14
by the State Travel Reimbursement Act, Section 500.1 et seq. of this
14
15
title, from funds available to the appropriate appointing authority.
15
16
B. The Office of Management and Enterprise Services shall
16
17
provide coordinate with the Commission to provide staff support to
17
18
the Oklahoma Commission on the Status of Women.
